- Screen's position starts at the top left corner always 
- Imagine the screen as a graph
- Graph always start at the top left corner with x = 0 & y = 0
- Any elements position also start at the top left corner
- x position of any elements will be from top left, meaning 0 to the position.
  - example: x = 10 then it will be 10 positin to the right of 0 
- y position of any elements will be from top left, meaning 0 to the position.
 - example: y = 10 then it will be 10 positin to the bottom of 0
